title: What channel is Texas Rangers-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALDS Game 4
text:
The Toronto Blue Jays fought off elimination on Sunday to force a Game 4 of their American League Divisional Series against Texas on Monday afternoon at Globe Life Park.
The Rangers lead the best-of-5 series two games to one.
R.A. Dickey is scheduled to get the start for Toronto against Derek Holland for Texas. Dickey is 8-1 with a 2.80 ERA in 15 starts since the All-Star break.
The game starts at 4 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1.
Here's how to find Fox Sports 1 in Central New York:
Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
